The paper proposes a data-driven framework for ranking paths based on historical trajectories using multi-task learning. It involves generating a compact set of training data, embedding each vertex to a feature vector, and applying recurrent neural network to model the sequence. This work involves machine learning, data mining, and spatial networks, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DB (Databases), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
